<L>Could &s;uch an<NOTE N="f" PLACE="foot"><HI>&V;nexhau&s;ted Trea&s;ure. The Fi&s;hery,</HI> and therefore very well propos'd to match the Trea&s;ures before &s;poken of, not only in its Value, but in this Peculiar, <HI>That 'tis never exhau&s;ted.</HI> Nor is it all the le&s;s for the Prodigious Quantities that are or might be Annually taken. Which &s;ome Authors have ob&s;erv'd, That they were enough to &s;ub&s;i&s;t the whole Nation, if there were no other Provi&s;ion. <Q><HI>Tanta Pi&s;cium e&s;t Exundantia, cum ubique tum quo magis ad Septentrionem accedas, ut vel ii &s;oli &s;ufficere po&s;&s;int ad pa&s;tum In&s;ulae totius:</HI> <BIBL>Boeth. de De&s;crip. Reg. Scot</BIBL></Q></NOTE> Unexhau&s;ted Trea&s;ure boa&s;t,</L>
